Reasoning: The paper discusses visual image exploration and similarity search, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of graphs and algorithms for building hierarchical image similarity graphs suggests a potential fit for multimedia (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.DL) sub-categories. The visual sorting and manipulation of images also suggests a potential fit for graphics (cs.GR).
